BASIC
 - .dtsi files are included files, while .dts files are final Device
    Trees.
      - .dtsi: will contain definition of SoC-level information (or sometimes
        definitions common to several almost identical boards).
      - .dts file contains the board-level information.
 - runtime representation of the loaded device tree:
     ls -l /sys/firmware/devicetree/base/
 - All Device Tree bindings recognized by the kernel are
 documented in Documentation/devicetree/bindings
